Nature's palette spills with grace,
In strokes of every shade and hue;
The world, a canvas we embrace,
On this glorious stage, anew.

In every scene, a breath reveals,
The beauty of the seasons' change;
From winter's chill to summer's feels,
Life's sacred dance is ever strange.

 - From "Nature's Canvas" by Jessie Redmond Fauset

- Jessie Redmond Fauset
